                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/499: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-30T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 30, 1929—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 30—7:37 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1060. Your 394, November 28, noon. According to the latest report from reliable
                    official sources at Mukden, Chinese have not yet fully accepted Soviet terms.
                    Nanking has not been party to preliminary telegraphic discussions and its
                    attitude so far remains undeclared.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
